@startuml assignment-bob-lifecycle

' The lifecycle of an Assignment-based Bob, from authoring through to
' termination. Domain-level: stages are named in framework vocabulary,
' edges in skill verbs. Substrate details (worktrees, panes, launcher
' files) and tracker mechanics (custom fields, link types) are out of
' scope. Closed states are terminal except Returned, which re-enters the
' pickup pool, and Delivered, which may fan out via /onward.

title Assignment-based Bob lifecycle

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundCorner 6
skinparam defaultFontName sans-serif

state "Authored\n(in pickup pool)"      as authored
state "Spawned\n(substrate allocated)"  as spawned
state "Claimed\n(claim complete)"       as claimed
state "Working"                         as working
state "Materialized\n(parlay watching)" as materialized
state "Delivered"                       as delivered <<terminal>>
state "Returned"                        as returned  <<terminal>>
state "Abandoned"                       as abandoned <<terminal>>
state "Onward fanout"                   as onward

[*]          --> authored     : ""/file"" or ""/delegate""
authored     --> spawned      : ""/spawn""\n(or ""/delegate"")
spawned      --> claimed      : ""vv assignment-claim""\n(first-turn body)
claimed      --> working      : Bob begins\nthe Route's work
working      --> materialized : ""/realize""
materialized --> delivered    : ""/closeout delivered""\n(PR merged)
working      --> returned     : ""/closeout returned""\n(stopped partway)
working      --> abandoned    : ""/closeout abandoned""\n(Assignment obsolete)
claimed      --> abandoned    : ""/closeout abandoned""\n(without entering Working)
delivered    --> onward       : ""/onward"" fanout\n(optional)

returned     --> authored     : re-enters pool
onward       --> spawned      : downstream Assignment picked up

abandoned    --> [*]
delivered    --> [*]

@enduml
